"title": "4135: demons, Jesus Christ's authority over",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4135: demons, jesus christ's authority over",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Demons are subject to the authority of Jesus Christ during his ministry and subsequently in the ministry of the church.</p>\n<h2>All spiritual powers are subject to Jesus Christ who has supreme authority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:19-Eph1:22\">EPH 1:19–1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38\">ROM 8:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10\">EPH 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:10\">COL 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Demons are powerless before Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Demons can only do what he permits</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:31-Matt8:32\">MAT 8:31–8:32</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:12-Mark5:13\">MRK 5:12–5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:32-Luke8:33\">LUK 8:32–8:33</a></p>\n<h3>Demons obey his command</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:18\">MAT 17:18</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25-Mark9:26\">MRK 9:25–9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:42\">LUK 9:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33-Matt9:34\">MAT 9:33–9:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:9\">MRK 16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a></p>\n<h3>Demons disperse at his word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:25\">MRK 1:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:35\">LUK 4:35</a></p>\n<h2>The name of Jesus Christ has power against demons</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's name is used by his disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17\">MRK 16:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:38-Mark9:39\">MRK 9:38–9:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:49-Luke9:50\">LUK 9:49–9:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17\">LUK 10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:18\">ACT 16:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ anticipates the misuse of his own name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:22-Matt7:23\">MAT 7:22–7:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:13-Acts19:16\">ACT 19:13–19:16</a> <em>an example where Jesus' name is used in cases of demon-possession--but not by Jesus Christ's disciples, and not successfully</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's disciples have delegated power over demons</h2>\n<h3>In Jesus Christ's own lifetime</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1\">MAT 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:7\">MAT 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14-Mark3:15\">MRK 3:14–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7\">MRK 6:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1\">LUK 9:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:13\">MRK 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17\">LUK 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:19\">LUK 10:19</a></p>\n<h3>In the ongoing ministry of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17\">MRK 16:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:16\">ACT 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:7\">ACT 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:18\">ACT 16:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:12\">ACT 19:12</a></p>\n<h2>Others will attempt to drive out demons</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:27\">MAT 12:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:19\">LUK 11:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:38\">MRK 9:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:49\">LUK 9:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:13-Acts19:15\">ACT 19:13–19:15</a></p>\n<h2>The final punishment of demons</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:4\">2PE 2:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:6\">JUD 1:6</a></p>",
